# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Line-ending policy
#
# Store every text file with LF in the repository AND check it out with LF on
# every platform, Windows included. This makes line endings deterministic and
# independent of each developer's core.autocrlf setting — which is the usual
# cause of "the whole file changed" diffs and CRLF (^M) surprises on GitHub.
#
# On Windows, pair this with:  git config core.autocrlf false
# After changing this file, renormalize the repo:  git add --renormalize .
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
* text=auto eol=lf

# Autotools inputs and shell scripts must keep LF endings, even on Windows
# checkouts with core.autocrlf=true. If configure.ac is checked out with CRLF,
# a regenerated configure script embeds literal \r characters in its file
# lists and breaks the build on macOS/Linux
# ("config.status: error: cannot find input file").
configure    text eol=lf
configure.ac text eol=lf
*.sh         text eol=lf
*.m4         text eol=lf
*.am         text eol=lf
*.in         text eol=lf
bootstrap    text eol=lf
ylwrap       text eol=lf
depcomp      text eol=lf
missing      text eol=lf
install-sh   text eol=lf
config.guess text eol=lf
config.sub   text eol=lf
config.rpath text eol=lf
mkinstalldirs text eol=lf

# Binary files: never apply EOL conversion, so they can't be corrupted.
*.zip binary
*.bin binary
*.png binary
*.gif binary
*.jpg binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
*.a   binary
*.o   binary
*.exe binary
*.dll binary
